body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Price Autos. My name is Gerald Price. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hi, Julie. Thank you for sharing that. To better assist you, could you please provide me with your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's the fifteenth of May, nineteen ninety-two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Julie. Next, could you share the last four digits of your social security number with me?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's four two eight seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing that information, Julie. Please know that we take your privacy seriously at Price Autos.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I appreciate that. I had some concerns.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Julie. Thank you for bringing it to our attention. Your feedback helps us to improve. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Thank you for your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Julie. Thank you for reaching out to us. Have a wonderful day.
